content:
Creating a Catalog Fulfillment 

To create a catalog fulfillment, go to Setup and search for Service Catalog. Select Process Automation, then Catalog Fulfillments. Click New and select an active flow as the base for your fulfillment.

Enter a name and description, then click Map Fields. The fields available on the selected flow will appear. Select the input fields you want to map to the fulfillment and click Decorate.

The flow inputs are mapped to fulfillment inputs. Use the Additional Questions dropdown to select the input that enables additional questions. Only one input can be marked with this flag.

To add or remove inputs, click Edit Mapping. You can only add inputs present on the active flow your fulfillment is based on. Make an input value required by selecting Required.

Save changes and you can edit, clone, and delete catalog fulfillments. However, you must unassociate all related catalog items before editing or deleting a fulfillment.

When cloning a catalog fulfillment, the new fulfillment doesn't come with any related catalog items. Share fulfillments with guest users to allow them to execute related catalog items.
title: Service Cloud Catalog Fulfillment
